sentences: She started her playback career with the song "Deena Dayalo Rama" for the film Arayannagalude Veedu under music director Raveendran.
"Enthe Nee Kanna" for Sasneham Sumitra won her the Kerala State Film Award for Best Singer in 2003.
She has sung 500 movie songs and has also sung and given music for a new album for the Art of Living foundation which was released in September 2006 by HMV worldwide.
She recently sang for an album by Ilayaraja, Thiruvasagam, which was released by Sony Music.
Since 2017, Gayatri withdrew from film music industry and started focussing on gazals.
She is now anchoring popular gazal show Khayal on Media One TV.
In 2019, she performed in Jashn-e-Rekhta, a three-day annual Urdu festival and in Urdu Heritage Festival, Delhi.
Gayathri was married to Dr. Sayij on 4 January 2005, but the couple later divorced.
Kerala State Film Award for Best Singer (2003) – Enthe Nee Kanna – Sasneham Sumitra
2012 :Asianet Television Awards for best playback singer -Agniputhri
Gayatri to perform in Raveendran Night at Swaralaya-2006
